# Platform/Infrastructure — AtlasOS Agent Rules

## Infrastructure Safety
- All Kubernetes manifests must pass dry-run validation before apply.
- All StatefulSet changes must be tested with Longhorn snapshot rollback.
- Never delete PVCs or PVs without explicit approval.

## GitOps Discipline
- Cluster state must match git manifests. Drift is a bug.
- All changes go through PR → review → merge → auto-deploy.
- Manual kubectl apply is only for emergencies and must be reconciled within 1 hour.

## Secrets Management
- All secrets must be stored in Vault, not in git or ConfigMaps.
- Secret references must use ExternalSecret or Vault injector annotations.
- Rotate secrets on schedule; never reuse expired credentials.

## Deployment
- Canary deployments for critical services (>= 2 replicas).
- PDB (PodDisruptionBudget) required for all HA services.
- Rollback automatically if readiness probes fail within 2 minutes of deploy.

## Autonomous Operations
- Auto-cordon nodes with persistent health issues.
- Auto-scale deployments based on HPA metrics.
- Auto-create drift detection reports weekly.
